Everybody's Famous on DVD

Funny and inspiring, this delightful comedy examines just how far some people will go for fame. Jean is an ordinary family man and factory worker who is certain that his only child, Marva, is destined to become a famous singing star. If only Jean could catch a break... and if only Marva could be discovered. In this quirky tale of the search for fame, follow the father-daughter duo as they set out to make their dream a reality, taking unexpectedly outrageous steps along the way.
